TikTok Omerta, Biden Media Games & The End of Pay TV

Welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon roundup of the best new j=
ournalism on Puck.

First up today, Matt Belloni and John Ourand break down the multibillion-do=
llar Sunday Ticket penalty facing the NFL, an antitrust reckoning that coul=
d could rapidly remake the world of live sports on streaming=E2=80=94and ac=
celerate the crack-up of linear TV.

Plus, below the fold: Eriq Gardner examines why Hollywood has been sitting =
on the sidelines as the TikTok ban heads to court. Dylan Byers and Peter Ha=
mby dig into the Washington media reckoning surrounding debate-gate. Then M=
arion Maneker examines how a decade of collectors entering the art world wi=
th an =E2=80=9Cinvestment mindset=E2=80=9D seems to have choked off the mar=
ket=E2=80=94and what happens if everyone decides to head for the exits all
at once.

